snippet: The visit of Khaled Meshal sought to convey a sense of victory over Israel in the recent eight-day clash.
abstract: Khaled Meshal, long-exiled leader of militant group Hamas, enters Gaza for first time in symbolically powerful visit that seeks to reinforce Hamas’s contention that it was victorious in eight-day clash with Israel.

byline.contributor: Fares Akram contributed reporting from Gaza, and Isabel Kershner from Jerusalem.

lead_paragraph: The visit of Khaled Meshal sought to convey a sense of victory over Israel in the recent eight-day clash.

headline.seo: Khaled Meshal, Hamas Leader, Makes First Visit to Gaza
headline.main: Political Leader of Hamas Visits Gaza for the First Time
headline.print_headline: Exiled Leader of Hamas Makes His First Visit to Gaza
